    "created_at": "2016-10-21T15:39:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-21T15:39:39Z",
    "body": "After a lot of time researching, it looks like the problem was with the shared memory in the device. It was just 8MB. When we increased the memory, it went smoothly.\n\nWe made this:\n- edit the file /etc/fstab and change /dev/shm value from 8M to 996M\n- mount -o remount /dev/shm\n\nThanks for the help!\n"
